headline: AbbVie forecasts 2026 profit above estimates on strong sales of newer immunology drugs
summary: Feb 4 () - AbbVie forecast 2026 profit above Wall Street estimates on Wednesday after posting a fourth-quarter results beat, fueled by strong ​demand for newer immunology drugs Skyrizi and Rinvoq and a smaller-than-expected ‌decline in sales of its older medicine Humira. The drugmaker has been relying on Skyrizi and Rinvoq ‌to counter a drop in Humira sales, which have been facing competition from cheaper biosimilars, or near copies of a biological drug.
